00:00:47.850 --> 00:00:51.160
I have always been
interested in media

00:00:51.160 --> 00:00:55.050
I started out my career
working as a movie executive.

00:00:55.050 --> 00:00:59.760
I was at Sony, and
MGM, and New Line.

00:00:59.760 --> 00:01:04.180
But when I had kids, I stepped
off my movie executive path,

00:01:04.180 --> 00:01:06.750
and I decided to
go back to school

00:01:06.750 --> 00:01:11.820
and study adolescent development
at UCLA, where I got a Ph.D.,

00:01:11.820 --> 00:01:14.270
and I totally
transformed my life.

00:01:14.270 --> 00:01:16.640
And while I was
getting the Ph.D.,

00:01:16.640 --> 00:01:20.260
I also decided to study
media effects on children.

00:01:20.260 --> 00:01:22.860
And I found out that
I was really excited

00:01:22.860 --> 00:01:26.180
about sharing this
information with parents,

00:01:26.180 --> 00:01:28.010
with anyone who was interested.

00:01:28.010 --> 00:01:31.280
And I would go out and
I'd talk to parents,

00:01:31.280 --> 00:01:33.700
and I'd find out they
were really scared,

00:01:33.700 --> 00:01:36.300
and they were very confused
about the Digital Age.

00:01:36.300 --> 00:01:38.050
Nobody knew what to do.

00:01:38.050 --> 00:01:40.140
And I myself was scared.

00:01:40.140 --> 00:01:43.210
My kids were growing
up at the same time

00:01:43.210 --> 00:01:46.340
as I was going to school.

00:01:46.340 --> 00:01:49.130
The Digital Revolution
was taking off.

00:01:49.130 --> 00:01:50.980
I was studying this stuff.

00:01:50.980 --> 00:01:53.060
And as I would go
and talk to parents,

00:01:53.060 --> 00:01:55.070
I would be feeling
the same issues,

00:01:55.070 --> 00:01:59.160
but what fear didn't
jive with the research

00:01:59.160 --> 00:02:01.040
that I was reading.

00:02:01.040 --> 00:02:03.070
And I was also watching
my own children

00:02:03.070 --> 00:02:06.020
growing up, and seeing them
thriving in the Digital Age.

00:02:06.020 --> 00:02:10.050
So when I graduated from school,
I decided to write this book,

00:02:10.050 --> 00:02:11.690
"Media Moms &amp; Digital Dads."

00:02:11.690 --> 00:02:13.260
It's about my research.

00:02:13.260 --> 00:02:15.200
It's about other
people's research.

00:02:15.200 --> 00:02:17.260
It takes a lot of
different topics,

00:02:17.260 --> 00:02:22.010
and I try to bottom
line it for parents,

00:02:22.010 --> 00:02:23.502
and I give takeaways and tips.

00:02:23.502 --> 00:02:25.210
So I'm trying to make
it useful, but also

00:02:25.210 --> 00:02:28.100
give you the facts, both the
positive and the negative.

00:02:28.100 --> 00:02:30.550
