drone parenting.

00:09:13.090 --> 00:09:14.580
And this is a drone parent.

00:09:14.580 --> 00:09:15.560
She filters.

00:09:15.560 --> 00:09:16.580
She monitors.

00:09:16.580 --> 00:09:17.910
She watches everything.

00:09:17.910 --> 00:09:20.810
Did anyone see the movie
"Men, Women, and Children?"

00:09:20.810 --> 00:09:23.500
It's a really good
movie to get an idea

00:09:23.500 --> 00:09:26.420
about what parents' reactions
are to the Digital Age,

00:09:26.420 --> 00:09:28.220
and how kids care
about this stuff.

00:09:28.220 --> 00:09:29.980
I write about in a book too.

00:09:29.980 --> 00:09:34.060
She is an over-monitoring,
over-controlling parent,

00:09:34.060 --> 00:09:37.030
and there are some
devastating consequences.

00:09:37.030 --> 00:09:38.700
And then lastly,
of course, there's

00:09:38.700 --> 00:09:43.000
the media mom and digital dad,
which is what I advocate for.

00:09:43.000 --> 00:09:45.960
It's a reasoned, calm approach.

00:09:45.960 --> 00:09:47.430
Media is not going away.

00:09:47.430 --> 00:09:48.370
Get the facts.

00:09:48.370 --> 00:09:50.230
Don't stick your
head in the stand.

00:09:50.230 --> 00:09:52.720
Don't be a drone
and overprotective.

00:09:52.720 --> 00:09:57.080
Be involved, but also let
them embrace this stuff,

00:09:57.080 --> 00:09:58.570
because they're gonna need it.

00:09:58.570 --> 00:10:02.792
So here are my four
recommendations.

00:10:02.792 --> 00:10:04.250
In the book, there's
tons of stuff.

