here, the American Academy

00:10:28.210 --> 00:10:31.460
of Pediatrics just came
out with some new--

00:10:31.460 --> 00:10:34.410
they're not guidelines yet,
but some advice for families.

00:10:34.410 --> 00:10:36.570
And they say content--
you'll see it

00:10:36.570 --> 00:10:40.360
in a second-- is more
important than time spent.

00:10:40.360 --> 00:10:43.180
So thinking about what
your kids are using,

00:10:43.180 --> 00:10:45.710
and what you're using,
and watching, and playing

00:10:45.710 --> 00:10:48.130
is important, more
important than anything.

00:10:48.130 --> 00:10:52.700
Build face-to-face time into
each day, co-view, co-play,

00:10:52.700 --> 00:10:55.450
and try to stay positive.

00:10:55.450 --> 00:10:56.930
So start with role modeling.

00:10:56.930 --> 00:11:02.480
This is a survey that was done
with 6,000 people, parents

00:11:02.480 --> 00:11:06.444
and kids, families
of kids 8 to 13.

00:11:06.444 --> 00:11:09.540
