00:13:07.454 --> 00:13:08.370
AUDIENCE: Drive what?

00:13:08.370 --> 00:13:09.536
DR. YALDA UHLS: Drive a car.

00:13:13.290 --> 00:13:14.946
Five.

00:13:14.946 --> 00:13:18.300
AAA says 5-years-old.

00:13:18.300 --> 00:13:20.660
I found this out when I
was taking the parent AAA

00:13:20.660 --> 00:13:22.790
class for my daughter.

00:13:22.790 --> 00:13:25.920
So if you don't want your
kid to grow up to be this,

00:13:25.920 --> 00:13:27.560
don't do this.

00:13:27.560 --> 00:13:31.390
That kid is actually
learning from her.

00:13:31.390 --> 00:13:33.440
Bottom line, responsible
role modeling

00:13:33.440 --> 00:13:36.270
means you should prioritize
face-to-face conversation.

00:13:36.270 --> 00:13:37.910
Now, that doesn't
mean that you have

00:13:37.910 --> 00:13:39.370
to never be on your device.

00:13:39.370 --> 00:13:40.620
That's unrealistic.

00:13:40.620 --> 00:13:42.040
A lot of times,
you're doing work.

00:13:42.040 --> 00:13:43.390
I'm on my device a lot.

00:13:43.390 --> 00:13:47.540
By the way, I'm guilty
of so many things.

00:13:47.540 --> 00:13:50.780
But when your child
wants your attention,

00:13:50.780 --> 00:13:52.010
try to give it to them.

00:13:52.010 --> 00:13:53.760
You don't have to do
it every single time.

00:13:53.760 --> 00:13:55.490
Often, it's awkward.

00:13:55.490 --> 00:13:58.725
But when I was growing up,
when my kids were growing up,

00:13:58.725 --> 00:14:00.110
I said 10 minutes on the floor.

00:14:00.110 --> 00:14:03.050
All the experts say spend
10 minutes on the floor

00:14:03.050 --> 00:14:04.800
with them, playing with them.

00:14:04.800 --> 00:14:06.100
That's still great advice.

00:14:06.100 --> 00:14:08.310
It's also great
advice to put down

00:14:08.310 --> 00:14:09.750
your device for 10 minutes.

00:14:09.750 --> 00:14:12.970
Make it clear that
they're your priority.

00:14:12.970 --> 00:14:15.100
Also, controlled
use of cell phones.

00:14:15.100 --> 00:14:16.690
So that's texting and driving.

00:14:16.690 --> 00:14:18.890
Don't do it while you're
walking across the street.

00:14:18.890 --> 00:14:21.570
Think about your
own cellphone use.

00:14:21.570 --> 00:14:24.280
Model technology as
a tool, not a treat.

00:14:24.280 --> 00:14:27.400
So that's my husband,
Jim Uhls over there.

00:14:27.400 --> 00:14:29.540
He is a screenwriter.

00:14:29.540 --> 00:14:32.090
He's probably very
embarrassed that I did that.

00:14:32.090 --> 00:14:35.900
He is a screenwriter, and
he's always on his computer.

00:14:35.900 --> 00:14:38.430
And he is working.

00:14:38.430 --> 00:14:42.016
That's what he has to do, but
