00:27:52.990 --> 00:27:56.330
There hasn't been much success
academically, at least,

00:27:56.330 --> 00:27:59.430
with some of those schools,
but video games in general

00:27:59.430 --> 00:28:02.270
are not the horrible thing
that a lot of parents

00:28:02.270 --> 00:28:03.300
think they are.

00:28:03.300 --> 00:28:04.860
They develop spatial skills.

00:28:04.860 --> 00:28:07.200
Do you guys know what
special skills are?

00:28:07.200 --> 00:28:09.970
You need them in
engineering, mental rotation,

00:28:09.970 --> 00:28:14.000
understanding how
things move in space.

00:28:14.000 --> 00:28:16.610
You use it when you park a car.

00:28:16.610 --> 00:28:19.090
They contribute to
success in STEM fields.

00:28:19.090 --> 00:28:21.020
There's tons of
research on this.

00:28:21.020 --> 00:28:24.140
And girls who play video games,
so the spatial component,

00:28:24.140 --> 00:28:27.230
they improve dramatically
in this arena.

00:28:27.230 --> 00:28:30.630
So there's actually a
difference in older girls

00:28:30.630 --> 00:28:32.140
in spatial skills.

00:28:32.140 --> 00:28:35.020
But if a girl can
play video games,

00:28:35.020 --> 00:28:37.150
you could almost
equalize the difference.

00:28:37.150 --> 00:28:39.720
And I describe several
experiments about that.

00:28:39.720 --> 00:28:44.300
And there's so many positive
effects with video games

00:28:44.300 --> 00:28:47.950
